    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2462188613" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2462188613" />
    <a title="Dale Harcombe" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4800708-dale-harcombe"><img alt="Dale Harcombe" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1380932680p2/4800708.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2462188613?book_show_action=true">Jul 23, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dale Harcombe" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dale Harcombe" href="/user/show/4800708-dale-harcombe">Dale Harcombe</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780544866461" href="/book/show/30971715-the-weight-of-ink">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2462188613" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17111300886562523766">Four and a half stars<br/> Helen Watt has been summoned to view a cache of seventeenth century documents discovered under the staircase in a large old house during renovations. With the help of Aaron Levy, and American graduate student, Helen begins work to piece together the identity of the scribe of these precious historical documents and find out who the elusive Aleph is. Sadly for them they don’t have unlimited time to uncover all the documents secrets as others have also been called in. So it is</span>
  <span id="freeText17111300886562523766" style="display:none">Four and a half stars<br /> Helen Watt has been summoned to view a cache of seventeenth century documents discovered under the staircase in a large old house during renovations. With the help of Aaron Levy, and American graduate student, Helen begins work to piece together the identity of the scribe of these precious historical documents and find out who the elusive Aleph is. Sadly for them they don’t have unlimited time to uncover all the documents secrets as others have also been called in. So it is a race against time as to who finds the truth first. As the documents are carefully examined the story tells of Ester Velasquez who emigrates from Amsterdam and comes under the tutelage of a rabbi who was blinded during the Inquisition. These two stories have the narrative shifting around in time but it is easy to get drawn into both narratives. <br />Both Ester and Helen are single minded, determined women, who may not always behave the way convention demands they should. Helen is also battling personal illness which is making life hard and why she had to enlist help from a younger, if somewhat brash colleague. Helen is an abrasive personality and yet likeable once the reader gets to know more of her story. I am not used to books taking me as long to read as this one did, (six days). This was firstly because it is a thick book 560 pages but also because this is a book that deserves time taken over it. If you are looking for a page turner, this is not it. It is a book to be read, thought about and savoured. When at times I started to get a little bored with some minor characters that seemed unnecessary, the author quickly drew me back again to the main story.<br />Anyone who likes historical fiction that has you thinking and wanting to know more of the times should find this an interesting read that is obviously well researched. I was glad to have read it and after seeing me engrossed and hearing my comments, my husband is now reading it. I can’t wait for him to finish it so we can talk about this this book. I would definitely recommend this book to anyone looking for a book that covers history, philosophical issues, religious beliefs, seeing how times have changed and that contains strong believable characters and a mystery.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17111300886562523766" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


